During a joint press conference in Beijing, Chinese President Xi Jinping and U.S. President Donald Trump discussed their commitments to deepening China-U.S. relations and addressing major international and regional issues. They emphasized the importance of a healthy and stable relationship between the two countries, highlighting the need for win-win cooperation. The leaders agreed to enhance communication and cooperation through various dialogue mechanisms, including economic, military, and cybersecurity dialogues. They also discussed economic cooperation, trade imbalance, and market access, with over $250 billion worth of commercial deals and investment agreements signed during the visit. Additionally, they reaffirmed their commitment to denuclearizing the Korean Peninsula and addressing other global challenges such as terrorism and drug trafficking. The leaders expressed their desire to promote people-to-people exchanges and work together on international issues to contribute to peace, stability, and prosperity.